      "snippet": "geocoder.geocode({ address: formattedAddress }, ...) // undefined variable! // ✅ FIXED geocoder.geocode({ address: address }, ...) // use parameter ``` The code was trying to geocode an **undefined variable**, so geocoding always failed → \"address not found\" error → Street View never rendered. ### **Impact** - This was a typo/variable scoping bug introduced during last rewrite - Explains why every test address returned \"address not found\" regardless of validity - Single-line fix; now deployed ### **Verification Steps** User should now test at: https://agentrocketman.com/index2.html 1. Enter Toronto address (e.g., \"100 King St W, Toronto\") 2. Click \"Check my address\" 3. Scroll down → St",
